
[1]purity

   PU'RITY, n. [L. puritas, form purus.]

   1. Freedom from foreign admixture or heterogeneous matter; as the
   purity of water, of wine, of spirit; the purity of drugs; the purity of
   metals.

   2. Cleanness; freedom from foulness or dirt; as the purity of a
   garment.

   The purity of a linen vesture.

   3. Freedom from guilt or the defilement of sin; innocence; as purity of
   heart or life.

   4. Chastity; freedom from contamination by illicit sexual connection.

   5. Freedom from any sinister or improper views; as the purity of
   motives or designs.

   6. Freedom from foreign idioms, from barbarous or improper words or
   phrases; as purity of style or language.
